claim.claim-text:
3. A method of indicating a connection state of an input/output cable via which an AT Attachment Packet Interface (ATAPI) drive communicates with a host, the method comprising:
when power is applied to the AT Attachment Packet Interface (ATAPI) drive, setting a flag that checks the connection state of the input/output cable;
if a command is not received from the host for a predetermined period of time after determining the flag is set, commanding a timer to increase a time counter; and
if the increased time exceeds a reference time, indicating that the input/output cable is not connected to the host,
wherein in commanding the timer to increase the time counter, if the command is received from the host within the predetermined period of time, the set flag is cleared.
